## Vercel Speed Insights Installation - Implementation Report

### Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for the Next.js App Router project following the latest official Vercel documentation (https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/quickstart).

### Changes Made

#### 1. Package Installation
- **Modified**: `package.json`
  - Added `@vercel/speed-insights` version `^2.0.0` to dependencies
  - Package installed using pnpm (the project's package manager)

#### 2. Component Integration
- **Modified**: `app/layout.tsx`
  - Imported `SpeedInsights` component from `@vercel/speed-insights/next`
  - Added `<SpeedInsights />` component to the root layout's body element
  - Placement follows Next.js App Router best practices (after children in body)

#### 3. Lock File Updates
- **Created**: `pnpm-lock.yaml`
  - Generated by pnpm to ensure consistent dependency resolution
  - Includes all necessary dependencies for @vercel/speed-insights

### Implementation Details

The implementation follows the official Vercel Speed Insights quickstart guide for Next.js 13.5+ with App Router:

1. **Framework Detection**: Identified the project uses Next.js with App Router (presence of `app/layout.tsx`)
2. **Package Manager**: Confirmed pnpm is the package manager (based on existing pnpm-lock.yaml)
3. **Installation**: Added the package using the correct Next.js-specific import path (`@vercel/speed-insights/next`)
4. **Component Placement**: Added the SpeedInsights component in the root layout's body element, ensuring it's included on all pages

### Verification Steps Completed

✅ **Build Test**: Successfully built the project with `pnpm build`
- All routes compiled without errors
- Production build completed successfully
- No TypeScript errors

✅ **Dependencies**: Verified all dependencies are installed correctly with `pnpm install`
- Lockfile is up to date
- No dependency conflicts

✅ **Code Structure**: Preserved existing code patterns
- Maintained consistent formatting
- No changes to existing functionality
- Added minimal, focused changes only

### Next Steps for Deployment

To complete the Speed Insights setup:

1. **Enable in Vercel Dashboard**:
   - Navigate to the Vercel project dashboard
   - Select "Speed Insights" from the sidebar
   - Click "Enable" to activate Speed Insights for the project

2. **Deploy**:
   - Push these changes to the repository
   - Vercel will automatically deploy with Speed Insights enabled
   - The Speed Insights script will be injected at `/_vercel/speed-insights/*`

3. **Verify**:
   - After deployment, check the deployed page's HTML source
   - Confirm the Speed Insights script is loaded
   - Visit the Vercel dashboard to view metrics once users access the site

### Technical Notes

- The `@vercel/speed-insights/next` package is framework-optimized for Next.js
- The SpeedInsights component automatically tracks Core Web Vitals
- No additional configuration is required for basic functionality
- The component is lightweight and has minimal performance impact
- Data will appear in the Vercel dashboard after the next deployment and user visits
